com.kremerk.Sqlite
Class WhereExecutor<T>

java.lang.Object
  com.kremerk.Sqlite.WhereExecutor<T>

public class WhereExecutor<T>
extends java.lang.Object

Used to specify an equality in a where statement. This is used in conjunction with SqlExecutor.where(String) and SqlExecutor.and(String).

like

public SqlExecutor<T> like(java.lang.String value)
Used to specify a like than comparison with the supplied value and the preceding field as specified with a where or and.

A like statement uses a % as the wild card and needs to be specified in the value string passed in.

Parameters:
value - The value for the right hand side of the like statement.

A SqlExecutor used for function chaining.
